                                                            GUIDE TO USING VULNERABILITY NAMING SCHEMES



   with vendors of scanning tools regarding false positives or false negatives will be clearer if the
   vulnerability is labeled by CVE or CCE name.

3. As recommended in NIST SP 800-117 Revision 1, organizations should encourage security
   software vendors to incorporate support for CVE and CCE into their products, as well as
   encourage all software vendors to include authoritative CVE and CCE names in their product
   security advisories and other security-related documentation and communications, as well as to
   reference the CPE names for their products.




